# API Testing Examples for Attendance Reminder System
# Use VS Code REST Client extension or curl commands

### 1. Test Cron Endpoint (Daily Automated Processing)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/cron/attendance-reminders
Authorization: Bearer test-secret-key-123

### 2. Process All Reminders (Admin)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/reminders
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

{
  "action": "process_all"
}

### 3. Process Reminders for Specific Course
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/reminders
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

{
  "action": "process_course",
  "courseId": 1
}

### 4. Process Reminder for Specific Student
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/reminders
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

{
  "action": "process_student",
  "studentId": "user-id-here",
  "courseId": 1
}

### 5. Get Email History
GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/reminders?action=history&limit=10
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

### 6. Get Attendance Statistics
GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/reminders?action=statistics&courseId=1
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

### 7. Enable Email Reminders for Course
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/settings
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

{
  "courseId": 1,
  "action": "enable"
}

### 8. Update Course Settings
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/admin/attendance/settings
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: better-auth.session_token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN

{
  "courseId": 1,
  "settings": {
    "lectureCount": 13,
    "labCount": 12,
    "attendanceThreshold": 0.80,
    "emailEnabled": true
  }
}